HEADWORD: Unisexual
<hw>U`ni*sex"u*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Uni-</ets>
+ <ets>sexual</ets>: cf. F. <ets>unisexuel</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Having one sex only, as plants which have the
male and female flowers on separate individuals, or animals in which the
sexes are in separate individuals; di⟦oe⟧cious; -- distinguished from
<xex>bisexual</xex>, or <xex>hermaphrodite</xex>. See
<er>Di⟦oe⟧cious</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

